&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;GitLab is the intelligent orchestration platform for DevSecOps. GitLab enables organizations to increase developer productivity, improve operational efficiency, reduce security and compliance risk, and accelerate digital transformation. More than 50 million registered users and more than 50% of the Fortune 100* trust GitLab to ship better, more secure software faster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The same principles built into our products are reflected in how our team works: we embrace AI as a core productivity multiplier, with all team members expected to incorporate AI into their daily workflows to drive efficiency, innovation, and impact. GitLab is where careers accelerate, innovation flourishes, and every voice is valued. Our high-performance culture is driven by our values&amp;nbsp;and continuous knowledge exchange, enabling our team members to reach their full potential while collaborating with industry leaders to solve complex problems. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OuZIb5zszQI&quot;&gt;Co-create the future with us&lt;/a&gt; as we build technology that transforms how the world develops software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*&lt;em&gt;Fortune 500® is a registered trademark of Fortune Media IP Limited, used under license. Claim based on GitLab data. Fortune 100 refers to the top 20% ranked companies in the 2025 Fortune 500 list, published in June 2025. Fortune and Fortune Media IP Limited are not affiliated with, and do not endorse products or services of GitLab.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An overview of this role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Senior Manager, Technical Architects on GitLab&#39;s AMER Professional Services team, you&#39;ll oversee one of the most technically credible and customer-facing groups in the organization. This team helps turn customer priorities into real adoption and measurable outcomes by guiding complex implementations, shaping new service patterns, and bringing emerging GitLab capabilities into production environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll own the AMER Technical Architecture practice across both presales and delivery, managing a team of Technical Architects who work on complex customer needs, early-stage offerings, and strategic engagements. This role is well suited for someone who can coach senior technical talent, bring structure to ambiguity, and keep the team focused on customer outcomes instead of task completion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your first year, you&#39;ll help strengthen how the practice operates across delivery quality, team development, resource planning, and consultative engagement management. You&#39;ll work alongside architects in areas including AI, security, and broader platform architecture, while helping the team turn what they learn in the field into repeatable methods that can scale across Professional Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some examples of our projects:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Running technical discovery, scoping, and delivery for complex Professional Services engagements in AMER&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turning early customer work on new GitLab capabilities into repeatable delivery kits, standards, and service patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and develop the AMER Technical Architecture team, including Intermediate, Senior, and Staff Technical Architects working across platform, AI, and security-related customer engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the practice end to end, covering presales collaboration, engagement scoping, technical delivery oversight, staffing, utilization, and forecast alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach architects to grow as credible advisors centered on customer outcomes, strong technical judgment, and consultative communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner on complex presales motions with Engagement Managers on estimation, solution framing, statement of work assumptions, and technical risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Join strategic customer conversations where senior technical expertise helps build credibility, clarify ambiguity, and improve the path to successful delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the team through first-mover delivery of new GitLab capabilities, helping shape how emerging offerings are tested, delivered, and improved in real customer environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turn lessons from strategic engagements into reusable templates, architecture guidance, migration patterns, and implementation standards that can be adopted by the broader Professional Services organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the Technical Architecture practice in AMER Professional Services management discussions and partner with adjacent functions to improve coordination, service evolution, and delivery consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience managing senior technical professionals in a services, consulting, or Professional Services environment, with a strong track record of coaching, performance management, and career development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience applying expertise in platform engineering, site reliability engineering, infrastructure, or software development to guide technical direction and build credibility with highly experienced architects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience running consultative engagements by linking technical work to business goals and keeping teams focused on customer value and realized outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with technically complex presales work, including discovery, scoping, estimation, solution definition, and risk assessment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to operate effectively in fast-moving environments where offerings, priorities, and organizational needs continue to evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building or improving repeatable delivery methods such as playbooks, standards, service kits, architecture patterns, or implementation guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience facilitating executive-level customer conversations, giving clear feedback, and aligning cross-functional stakeholders around delivery direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with GitLab-relevant domains such as AI-powered developer workflows, security, DevSecOps, or enterprise platform adoption is helpful, along with experience ramping up quickly in adjacent areas where needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Professional Services team helps customers adopt GitLab in ways that create lasting value. Within that organization, the Technical Architecture team handles some of the most complex and ambiguous work. This includes shaping early delivery approaches for new capabilities, contributing to high-impact customer engagements, and creating the patterns that help the wider organization scale successful services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll manage the AMER team of Technical Architects and work closely with Engagement Management, Professional Services Operations, Customer Experience Engineering, and other Professional Services colleagues. We play an important role in setting the technical standard for delivery while also helping define how new services should be scoped, delivered, and improved over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitLab works in an all-remote, asynchronous environment built on transparency, iteration, collaboration, and empowered ownership. In our team, that means giving managers and architects the latitude to solve hard problems, exchange what they learn openly, and continuously improve how the practice runs. If you enjoy developing strong technical talent, creating clarity in fast-changing environments, and helping customers succeed through thoughtful consulting, you&#39;ll have a meaningful place to make an impact with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The base salary range for this role’s listed level is currently for residents of the&amp;nbsp;United States only. This range is intended to reflect the role&#39;s base salary rate in locations throughout the US.&amp;nbsp;Grade level and salary ranges are determined through interviews and a review of education, experience, knowledge, skills, abilities of the applicant, equity with other team members, alignment with market data,&amp;nbsp;and geographic location.&amp;nbsp;The base salary range does not include any bonuses, equity, or benefits. See more information on our &lt;a class=&quot;waffle-rich-text-link&quot; href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/&quot; data-sheets-formula-bar-text-link=&quot;https://bit.ly/GLBeneUS&quot; data-sheets-formula-bar-text-style=&quot;font-size:12px;color:#1155cc;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:underline;font-family:&#39;&#39;Arial&#39;&#39;;font-style:normal;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;&quot;&gt;benefits&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-formula-bar-text-style=&quot;font-size:12px;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;font-family:&#39;Arial&#39;;font-style:normal;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;&quot;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;waffle-rich-text-link&quot; href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/stock-options/&quot; data-sheets-formula-bar-text-link=&quot;https://bit.ly/GLequity&quot; data-sheets-formula-bar-text-style=&quot;font-size:12px;color:#1155cc;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:underline;font-family:&#39;&#39;Arial&#39;&#39;;font-style:normal;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;&quot;&gt;equity&lt;/a&gt;. Sales roles are also eligible for incentive pay targeted at up to 100% of the offered base salary.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;United States Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$171,360&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$288,660 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How GitLab Supports Full-Time Employees&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/&quot;&gt;Benefits to support your health, finances, and well-being&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/people-group/time-off-and-absence/time-off-types/#flexible-paid-time-off-pto&quot;&gt;Flexible Paid Time Off&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/company/culture/inclusion/tmrg-tmag/&quot;&gt;Team Member Resource Groups&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/stock-options/&quot;&gt;Equity Compensation &amp;amp; Employee Stock Purchase Plan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/people-group/learning-and-development/growth-and-development/&quot;&gt;Growth and Development Fund&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/#parental-leave&quot;&gt;Parental Leave&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that we welcome interest from candidates with varying levels of experience; many successful candidates do not meet every single requirement. Additionally, studies have shown that people from &lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/company/culture/inclusion/#examples-of-select-underrepresented-groups&quot;&gt;underrepresented groups&lt;/a&gt; are less likely to apply to a job unless they meet every single qualification. If you&#39;re excited about this role, please apply and allow our recruiters to assess your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Country Hiring Guidelines: &lt;/strong&gt;GitLab hires new team members in countries around the world. All of our roles are remote, however some roles may carry specific location-based eligibility requirements. Our Talent Acquisition team can help answer any questions about location after starting the recruiting process.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
